SNL After Lorne, ESPN=E2=80=99s Media Moneyball, Abercrombie &
Rich
--------------------------------------------------------

Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon digest featuring Puck=E2=
=80=99s best new
reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Eriq Gardner offers a provocative assessment of casino magn=
ate Steve Wynn=E2=80=99s circuitous bid for the Supreme Court to reconsider=
 New York Times Co. v. Sullivan and the =E2=80=9Cactual malice=E2=80=9D lib=
el standard. Sure, the landmark ruling has long been a heat shield for publ=
ishers, but is the current legal framework the best we can do?=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Peter Hamby picks through exclusive (and surprising) =
polling data on Dems=E2=80=99 media habits, the residual goodwill toward Ka=
mala Harris, and some =E2=80=9928 celebrity alternatives. Julie Davich offe=
rs an expert assessment of the growing market for the enigmatic surrealist =
Gertrude Abercrombie. And Sarah Shapiro
evaluates whether fresh financing for Sarah Staudinger=E2=80=99s beloved, d=
ecade-old fashion brand can actually help it scale.

=C2=A0

Meanwhile, on the pods: Matt Belloni and Lucas Shaw link up on The Town to =
